		<hr size="1">Soloing for a Paladin is one of the hardest things you'll EVER do IMHO.<BR>The most OPTIMAL way to do it is to find a place with some undead in an open area and fear kite them.  You'll need sow to keep up with them unless you have some way to snare, but otherwise if pathing is good and you're patient, it isn't that hard... just time consuming. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/ohwell.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle><BR>Early in life(20-30), it IS possible to solo live beings using the standard "hack-and-slash and pray ya live" tactic, but as you level this gets MUCH harder and at my level(54), is all but impossible.</P><P>That's about all I can come up with for right now.  If I think of anything else useful, I'll post it here for ya. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P><BR>Teluas Truesword<BR>54th season Cavalier of Tunare<BR>Quellious server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
